abstract: Ahead of two major shows, the painter Jonas Wood reflects on his early career â€” and the most unusual object in his studio.
snippet: Ahead of two major shows, the painter Jonas Wood reflects on his early career â€” and the most unusual object in his studio.
lead_paragraph: Jonas Woodâ€™s East Hollywood studio â€” a refurbished industrial space hidden behind a razor-wired metal gate â€” is populated with the familiar objects that appear in his paintings. There are colonies of potted plants and basketball paraphernalia that ranges in size from plush couch cushions to man-sized orbs. Every room is filled with art, most notably by the ceramist Shio Kusaka, Woodâ€™s studio mate and wife, and Kiki and Momo, their son and daughter.

abstract: Deap Ubhi has spent his tech career bouncing around. Now heâ€™s tangled up in a little battle over one of the biggest government I.T. contracts in history.
snippet: Deap Ubhi has spent his tech career bouncing around. Now heâ€™s tangled up in a little battle over one of the biggest government I.T. contracts in history.
lead_paragraph: Deap Ubhi is a restless guy. At 26, he quit his job in private equity in Northern California, where he had grown up and gone to college, and then moved to India to found Burrp!, a local search site similar to Yelp. He sold the company in 2009 and along with other alums became what they called the Burrp! mafia, seeding and growing other start-ups in India.
